Results.ReviewText:
I have been drinking gold blend coffee for a long time I have tried other brands but gold blend is the best. I have just sampled your new gold blend in tescos this morning and yes its another winner for nescafe a nice strong and smooth taste.
so I brought two jars.
Results.Title: Gold blend coffee the best strong black and smooth

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, thank you for getting in touch with us. That's roast and ground coffee! It's nothing to be alarmed about and its actually a sign of quality coffee. After testing many recipes with our consumers, this recipe was the one they loved the most. We're really disappointed to hear you are not enjoying it, however we have added roast and ground coffee ground 10 times finer to give it a more intense aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. We are passing all comments onto the team and want to thank you again for the comment.

Results.ReviewText: I am so disappointed. I have used Gold Blend for years and do not like this new product. Towards the end of drinking a cup of coffee, I find it has a powdery effect which catches at the back of my throat. I fear I will have to look for a new brand of instant coffee
Results.Title: Changed but not for the better

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi, we're really sad to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made recently. 

That's roast and ground coffee at the bottom of your mug and nothing to be alarmed by. We’ve added this to our recipe recently. For more information, watch this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

We've made a note of your feedback & will be passing your comments on to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: We have been drinking Gold Blend all our lives but now find the taste and aroma disappointing and both the caffeinated and decaf versions leave dregs in the bottom of the mug.  All very disappointing and we shall certainly not be purchasing any more Nescafé coffee.
Results.Title: Huge change for the worse

ClientResponses.Response: That isn't what we like to hear but thank you very much for taking the time to let us know! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! We'll make a note of your comments & pass them to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: I dislike the taste and the powder left at the bottom of the cup. Today have managed to purchase 2 large jars of the original there were 4 left on theshelf and I am seriosly contemplating going back to get them if they are still there. I know my Mum feels the same
Results.Title: Do not like it

Results.ReviewText: I tried Gold blend as my normal coffee was unavailable. I found Gold blend to have a smooth taste with a hint of cream and a fresh aroma which gave rise to a superior quality taste which was not bitter. Gold blend is most suitable for drinking throughout the day.
Results.Title: A smooth blend for everyday use

Results.ReviewText:
Ive been buying Nescafe Gold Blend for many years and i can honestly safe i love the stuff!!
Love the taste and i have 2 cups every morning before work to kick me into gear :-)
Its smooth aroma and nice balance of not to over powering taste is a hit with me....
Results.Title: Love The Stuff!!!

Results.ReviewText: I buy this everytime. I find that it is the best on the market for instant coffee. I drink it black no sugar. So I find a lot of coffee to harsh or there is chickary blended in to other coffee. The only other coffee's I buy are the gold blend black and Barristia.
Results.Title: Great for all day

Results.ReviewText: There are many pretenders trying to stake a claim for king of the instants,  but for me and my family,  nothing had ever come close to the quality and finesse of Nescafe Gold Blend. It's  the original premium coffee  and still the best.  Truly the gold standard.
Results.Title: Gold Blend is king of the instant coffees

Results.ReviewText: Gold blend has a taste all its own, satisfyingly smooth and creamy with no bitter after taste. I like to drink it made with one part water to two parts semi-skimmed milk as this really accentuates the flavour. The quality of Gold Blend is consistently excellent.
Results.Title: My 11a.m. Treat!

Results.ReviewText: I bought this as I could not find a bottle of my usual Nescafe Gold Blend and the product tastes very similar to what I am used to. I just assumed that it was a rebranding/pakaging-change exercise. My go-to instant when I wake up. Prefer it to any other instant.
Results.Title: Decent instant coffee

ClientResponses.Response: We’re always wanting to improve the product for our loyal fans! After receiving feedback, we've added roast and ground coffee to our blend, to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. Watch this video to learn more: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

Results.ReviewText: Why you have changed from the original Nescafé gold to include coffee sludge in the bottom of the cup is a big mistake. Go back to the old saying “if it ain’t broke don’t fix it”
Results.Title: Coffee sediment not needed

Results.ReviewText: My office and i take turns to buy coffee, on my turn i tried the Gold range having not tried this in the office before,  we all loved it, the smell was the first thing we all noticed and the taste is so smooth and rich, such a lovely coffee, will all buy again.
Results.Title: Rich, captivaing coffee

Results.ReviewText: Tried this in October and its a perfect cup of rich, soothing, smooth coffee. It can get me up and going in the morning and when I get home it's perfect to relax with. It's well balanced, has an appealing rich aroma and it's difficult to stop at one smooth cup.
Results.Title: Perfect pick me up

Results.ReviewText: Bought this when my other regular coffee ran out, and I was really pleasantly surprised! The taste is great (in fact the only reason i gave it 4 instead of 5 stars is because it's just a tiny bit too weak for me), as is the value and everything. Great product!
Results.Title: Really tasty, great flavour and quality

Results.ReviewText:
i bought this in tesco , i normally have the ground coffee from nescafe but thought i would give it a try
i found it very smooth and easy to drink  , no after bitter taste.
the rest of my family love it too , so will have to go and buy another jar very soon
Results.Title: very smooth

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying this coffee for at least five years. For a coffee of this price it has a nice rich flavour, and it not too bitter. I couldn't wake up in the morning with out a nice mug of it before shower time.  It puts me in a good mood for the day ahead.
Results.Title: Anytime is Nescafe Gold Blend time

Results.ReviewText: I couldn't get hold of my usual brand and bought gold blend instead as it was on offer, wow 15 years later nothing else is drunk in our house! You know when someone gives you a diff brand, as gold blend is so smooth and luxurious it is instantly recognisable.
Results.Title: Tastes as good as a coffee shop brew

Results.ReviewText: Gold Blend has been our coffee of choice since its launch!  Sadly the change to the product is lacking in flavour and leaves sediment in the bottom of the cup.  We are seeking an alternative for the first time.
Results.Title: Change of product

Results.ReviewText: I was in a hurry and grabbed this coffee when I was in the supermarket .It was the best rush buy ever.As soon as I made a cup I new I had made a great buy. The aroma was mouth watering and the taste was just bliss. I will definitely be  buying Nescafe again.
Results.Title: Coffee bliss

Results.ReviewText: I usually drink Nescafe original, but decided to try Nescafe Gold Blend.  I enjoy this mid-morning and mid-afternoon.  It is a delicious, smooth coffee that suits my mood for 11's and mid-afternoon.  So now, I have the best of both worlds, thank you Nescafe!
Results.Title: Smooth

Results.UserLocation: Cheshire West and Chester, United Kingdom
Results.ReviewText: Bought when on offer to try as I am not a massive coffee drinker.  Now I enjoy a coffee regularly as it not bitter like some I have tried and been put off from. Will buy when not on offer too!  Tip - put milk in before boiling water as it sure tastes better.
Results.Title: Nice and smooth

Results.ReviewText: I buy this brand of coffee not only for use at home but also for use for our employees in the office.  Its smooth silky taste cannot be copied by any other brand, it just wouldn't taste the same.  There would be uproar if we used anything else in the office.
Results.Title: Lovely Warming Coffee Taste

Results.ReviewText: I bought this coffee a few months ago after not drinking coffee for years , I was amazed by the flavour , smoothness and aroma ..so now after a days work I come home kick my shoes off and relax with a nice cup of gold blend ...wouldn't drink anything else .
Results.Title: Brilliant cup of coffee

Results.ReviewText:
look, not going to lie. I am a tea drinker hectic over her. Butttt, coffee helps me get through the long days at work (12 hours shifts!).
It does it's job of waking me up, no bitter aftertaste and only needs one sugar to make me happy. What more is needed?
Results.Title: not quite as good as tea, but good for coffee!

Results.ReviewText: We have been buying this for years and serve it as an everyday or afterdinner drink - the taste fits both bills perfectly.  It is excellent value for a general smooth rich coffee and ofc there is the black for days when you need something a little stronger!
Results.Title: Great Taste Always

Results.ReviewText: Nescafé Gold Blend, I can't remember who introduced us to Gold Blend,well over eight years ago, but I'm so glad they did. I've tried a lot of different coffees,but Gold Blend is by far our favourite. Best of all is when we open a new jar. That aroma, "wow".
Results.Title: We love are Gold Blend.

Results.ReviewText: I never enjoy any other coffee than Gold Blend with caffeine.  I have to drink it with evaporated milk as a rule, but if that is not available, then I will drink it anyway.  Black, white, without sugar - with sugar if someone makes a mistake.  Just love it.
Results.Title: This is my favourite coffee in the world!

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe Gold Blend is the only instant coffee I will buy. It is, quite simply, delicious. It may not be the cheapest coffee around, but one gets what one pays for, and it is well worth the cost. Serve it fairly strong for an invigorating coffee experience.
Results.Title: Best instant coffee there is.
